    <taskbody>
        <context>
            <p>Copying information in CWRC-Writer can at times be a daunting task, but we provide
                the option to make sure you know exactly what you have copied before you paste
                it.</p>
        </context>
        <prereq>
            <p>Copy a portion of text in CWRC-Writer (see instructions at:)</p>
            <ul id="ul_chw_vsz_dp">
                <li><xref href="Copy_Paste_Text.dita"/></li>
                <li><xref href="Copy_Paste_Multiple_Tags.dita"/></li>
            </ul>
        </prereq>
        <steps id="steps_o2t_xyg_dp">
            <step>
                <cmd>Click on the small arrow at the bottom of the CWRC-Writer window/frame.</cmd>
                <stepresult>This will bring up the <cmdname>Validation</cmdname> and
                        <cmdname>Selection</cmdname> Tabs.</stepresult>
            </step>
            <step>
                <cmd>Click on the <cmdname>Selection</cmdname> tab.<image placement="break"
                        href="https://cwrc.ca/islandora/object/cwrc%3A6ae8bfa5-b68a-4c0c-b12d-93620c568437/datastream/OBJ/view"
                        id="image_pxl_bps_3x" align="center" scale="80"/></cmd>
            </step>
        </steps>
        <result>You will be able to see what you have copied, included the tags and text.
